'''Naâma''' ([[Arabic language|Arabic]]: <big>النعامة</big> or <big>نعامة</big>) is a [[municipalities of Algeria|municipality]] in [[Naâma Province]], [[Algeria]], of which it is the [[Capital (political)|province seat]]. It is coextensive with the [[districts of Algeria|district]] of Naâma and has a population of 8,256, (in 1998) which gives it 7 seats in the [[People's Municipal Assembly|PMA]]. Its population is 16,251 as per the census of 2008.
Its [[List of postal codes in Algeria|postal code]] is 45000 and its municipal code is 4501. Its telephone code is 049 nationally, or +213 49 internationally.
